61. make a bash script file 
	-- first create a file and put linux command into (cal)
	-- make permission into executable mode
	-- run the script file (./filename)

	






============ process ====================
 1. How to force kill process in Linux
	Use the pidof command to find the process ID of a running program or app
	$ pidof appname
2. To kill process in Linux with PID immediately:
	$ kill -9 pid
3. Want to kill process in Linux with application name forcefully? Try:
	$ killall -9 appname
4. You can sent -15 (SIGTERM) signal to process requesting it to terminate gracefully:
	$ killall -15 your-app-name
	AND
kill -15 pid





